# Dev-only persisted snapshots from /api/test/run
artifacts/api-server/data/archetype-history.json
# Stray copy created when the api-server is launched with cwd=artifacts/api-server
# (e.g. via `pnpm --filter`); the canonical default path is resolved via
# process.cwd() so a non-root cwd lands the file inside this nested dir.
artifacts/api-server/artifacts/

# Runtime state (curated defaults live in DEFAULT_MARKERS in code; reviewers mutate this at runtime via /feedback/calibration/handwavy-phrases)
artifacts/api-server/data/handwavy-phrases.json

# Runtime state (per-IP cooldown timestamps for the calibration-auth brute-force alerter; safe to delete to clear cooldown)
artifacts/api-server/data/calibration-auth-brute-force-state.json

# Runtime state (per-replica scheduler heartbeats and dedup state for AVRI drift
# notifications; rebuilt automatically by lib/avri-drift-notifications.ts on
# every replica boot and during scheduler ticks). Tracking it causes endless
# rebase conflicts as different replicas write their own heartbeat entries.
# Both paths are covered: the canonical location is artifacts/api-server/data/
# (process.cwd() is the workspace root); when the api-server is launched with
# cwd=artifacts/api-server (e.g. via `pnpm --filter`), it instead writes to
# artifacts/data/ via the same relative resolver.
artifacts/api-server/data/avri-drift-notifications.json
artifacts/data/avri-drift-notifications.json
